MUSICIAN Toya Delazy and his wife, Allison, have a bun in the oven. Toya announced the news on social media where she posted pictures of her touching Allison’s tummy. The musician, who is also the granddaughter of IFP founder Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi, said she’s going to be a mummy and thanked the universe for choosing them to be parents. “And just like that... Guide us universe, as we walk into this next chapter of our lives. Thank you for choosing us to bring forth this beautiful life force. We know it’s an incredible gift and miracle. I love you my gorgeous @alissonchaig doing this with you is one of the most incredible experiences. I couldn’t have chosen a better soul to build umuzi kamama,” she wrote. ALSO READ : CASE AGAINST FRESH AND EUPHONIK NOT REOPENED! “Here’s to the part called motherhood. Livumile, we’re pregnant. I’m gonna be a mommy,” she continued. This comes months after the couple got married. They tied the knot in October 2021 after celebrating 10 years as a couple. When Toya announced their wedding she wrote: “Ngiyathokoza mvelinqanga sekwenzekile. Now for the celebration next year @alissonchaig I choose you ngiyakuthanda ngenhlizo yam yonke also this pic is what fam is about. Thank you for holding us safe loves ngiyathokoza.” A post shared by Toya Delazy (@toyadelazy) 